               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 3 works (items a-c)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Collection of miscellaneous Persian works on Sufism, comprised of heterogeneous parts from differing sources. Volume not dated; individual items dated (items b and c), 1052-11 Shavvāl 1086/1642-29 December 1675. Variable naskh, nastaʿlīq and shikastah āmīz hands. Continuous stamped foliation with discontinuous Persian foliation. Loose folded paper wrapper (ledger, probably from an Acquittance Roll, dated August [year missing], Calcutta), upper and lower parts missing, watermarked (initials VEIC, E WISE, 1831); torn, stained, and incomplete. Lacks original binding. Folios unbound; cropped, later repairs, stains, and wormholes. Condition, extremely fragile. Valuation notes and owners’ seals.</summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1173-item1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="32v">ff. 1r-32v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. </p>
                        <p>Treatise apparently epitomising a larger unidentified work on Sufism, describing macrocosmic phenomena through microcosmic analogy, based on the theories of Ibn al-ʿArabī, here composed by the author ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz ibn Muḥammad al-Nasafī (d. circa 661/1262). 
</p>
                        <p>The work consists of two bāb, each subdivided into three aṣl. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Varied nastaʿlīq hands. 
</p>
                        <p>Detached folded interleaf between folios 32-33, with the Arabic draft of a letter addressed to a certain General Muḥammad Ismāʿīl, not dated or signed. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21104">al-Mabdāʾ va al-maʿād</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21104">المبداء و المعاد</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658820.0x000001 viaf_84084776"> ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz ibn Muḥammad al-Nasafī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658820.0x000001 viaf_84084776">عزيز ابن محمّد النّسفى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1173-item2">
                     <locus from="33v" to="94v">ff. 33v-94v</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1064">Jām-i jahān numāy</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1064">جام جهان نماى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Commentary conventionally attributed to <persName key="viaf_45899361" role="att">Vajīh al-Dīn ʿAlavī Gujarātī</persName> (d. 998/1590) writing on the Ṣūfī treatise <title>Jām-i jahān numā</title> ascribed to either to Muḥammad Shīrīn Maghribī (d, 809/1406-7) or Mīr Ghiyās̲ al-Dīn Manṣūr Shīrāzī (d. 948/1541), classifying the types and registers of existence and encounters with the divine. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dared colophon (f.94v): completed 11 Shavvāl 1086/29 December 1675. 
</p>
                        <p>This copy contains two diagrams (ff. 43v, 52v-53r). 
</p>
                        <p>Novel form of compressed text within limited folio space in anticipation of the second diagram, with lines composed of oblique units of text stacked on top of each other in linear formation (ff. 49v-52v). 
</p>
                        <p>Annotations and corrections in margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Collation note at end. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1173-item3">
                     <locus from="95v" to="162r">ff. 95v-162r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Commentary by the Ṣūfī saint, Valī ibn Mulūk Shāh al-Ṣiddīqī al-Qādirī (d. 998/1590), paraphrasing in Persian the Arabic work <title>Risālat al-Ghaws̲̲īyah</title>, conventionally ascribed to either Shaykh ʿAbd al-Qādir al-Jīlānī (d. 561/1166) or, according to Brockelmann and supported by Arberry, to Ibn al-ʿArabī (d. 638/1240). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 162r), cut and pasted onto last folio: completed 1052/1642. 
</p>
                        <p>Awkward but legible nastaʿlīq and naskh hands.
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7636" type="supplied">Valī ibn Mulūk Shāh al-Ṣiddīqī al-Qādirī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7636" type="supplied">ولى ابن ملوك شاه الصّدّيقى القادرى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21709">Sharḥ-i Ghaws̲̲īyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21709">شرح غوثيّه</title>
                  </msItem>
